Money Itinerary
Dec. 4- 7- Dollar remains officially 4,200 billion or 4.20 gold mark, in New York 4,100,000 - in other words the paper mark is more valuable than the "wecthe stäudiges" money. 
Dec 8.- In New York 2,500,000 still 4,200 billion.

Money- from autograph page
SIDE TRIPS
from Oct. 2 4 to about the 1 or 2, the government kept the official price of the Mark at 62,000,000,000 altho from the Jews on the street one could get 70 & 75.- Of course one knew a break was coming - 
On strike through: Monday Saturday, it stood officially 320 - on the street we were getting 400.
On Monday - Nov. 5 - still 320 getting 500 & 600. - 
On Nov. 6 - official 420 - on the street 800 - in the evening 1 billion -  
Nov. 7 - offical 600 - on the street 2 billions.- 
Of course there were riots again, but the "gold auliche" + " Dollarschatz auliche" are being used more + more + it may be a turn for the better.

SIDE TRIPS
Nov. 8 - 15 about - they kept the dollar officially at from 600 to 1,200 Millions While on the street one got up to four billion. Prices in restaurants, etc. jump with the dollar on the street, so that one would have to pay infinitely more to live here than at home if one couldn't exchange on the street. -

Nov. 19  - Official 2,520 - on the street 4,800 Million

Nov. 24 - Official 4,200 - on the street in Berlin 7,300 - + when I left 6,800 - 
Nov. 27-30 - Dollar sinking, 
Dec. 3 - Dollar 4,600,000 in New York - from 8,000,000,000

On the Monday following at 2,5000,000,000 + on Thurs. Oct. 18 again at 7 milliard. 
However prices are gradually being figured in gold mark basis - food in restaurants still being cheaper than eating at home - 30 pfenig in a good "beer [?local?]"
Oct. 21 < 20,000,000,000

INCIDENTS
(opproximate) 1923
Mark stood at Brennen 115,000 on June 24 - Went up to 80,000,000 25th. Sank gradually stood at 215,000 July 18th and at 283,000 " 24th Dropped from it 24th to 29th to 1,000,000 jumping from 500,000 to 750,000 almost overnight.   Has stood at 1,000,000 (about) for almost a week but banks refuse to give more than a certain amount of money (August 2, 3, 4) - Aug 2 - 1,000,000 cash, rest in checks, no American money - Aug. 3+4 - nothing - We pay by check - promissory notes in other words. - They have our money for which

PLACES VISITED
DATE June 26th
PLACE Berlin
Arrived in morning. Went over downtown Berlin Saw Brandenburg Thor + Unter den Linden- Went shopping - drove thru Sieges allie - ate at Habel  Restaurant - Walked [?] Museum Island etc. Seeing[?], castles, embassies, museums - buildings are so perfectly like like their pictures one is not at all disappointed - and the streets are immaculate. -

PLACES VISITED
DATE June 26 - afternoon
PLACE Potsdam - 
"Sans Souci  ist echt koiglich"  - I don't know who said it but it certainly describes the place - "?" I have heard people go into raptures over it but the reality far surpasses any description however vivid, that I have heard. It was a beautiful day - blue sky + sun and the coloring with the flowers + [?many?] trees, white statues, yellow castle, was

PLACES VISITED
DATE
PLACE
lovely beyond description. The mill stands there just as it is pictured - the terraces are there - everything -  we did not go into the castle itself because it was too late. - we ate supper on the porch of a hotel on the Havel just as the moon was rising - the sun setting at the same time - To make the end of a perfect day a shower came up + a rainbow appeared right above the trees,

PLACES VISITED
DATE
PLACE
sunset, moonlight + rainbow all at once - green trees, quiet, it cant be forgotten - (We also saw the ? and part of the Grunewald.)
June 27th
Accompanied Mrs. M Leueg? - +Katherine McK. To Flying Field + saw them leave for Munich. Met two nice America boys who were flying to Leipsic + had been traveling since October all around the world. - Was taken thru aerodromes &

PLACES VISITED 
DATE 
PLACE Berlin
shown the different planes by one of the Wacht polizies who had been a flier during the war.  Met a man from the Ruhr district - had to walk most of way in Ruhr  because of no trains - Wandered around Berlin - alone + on my own responsibility for the first time.  Invited for supper by Dr. Martin . Rode  to Charlottenburg alone. got off at Bismarck strasse (rode 3rd, class on underground) & crossed the

PLACES VISITED
DATE
PLACE
?Hardenberg? strasse which papa has mentioned. Delightful evening with the Martins - she is an artist (portrait work), he plays piano very well - 

  Thursday - June 28 - I walked around down town Berlin by myself - from the Friedrichstrasse to the Brandenburg Thor + thru the Tiergarten to the Königin Louisen [?Denbenal?]] + back to the Wilhelmsplatz - Left  Berlin early in the afternoon for Liebenstein

PLACES VISITIED
DATE June 28th
PLACE En Route from Berlin to Eisenach
To Halle the country is flat + rather reminds me of the vicinity of chicago. After Corbetha, however, (battles of Lützen, + Rossbach fought near here) it grew very interesting -                            Passed Kösen and saw my first real, lovely legendary castle squatting on top of the first ? Thuringian Hills - the Rudelsberg + coming right on top of it at a bend in the Saale -Sasleck, just two towers one with a piece bitten out of the

PLACES VISITED 
DATE 
PLACES
top, framed in greens. Passed thru Weimar + Erfurt - Beyond Neudietendorf I got my first thrill of seeing where the ? played. - We passed  the "Drei Gleichen"+ could clearly distinguish the castles at the top. The stories seem more vivid than ever now - Beyond Gotha we followed the Hörsel + the Hörselberg but I could not see much because it was on the other side of the train unluckily.

PLACES VISITED
DATE June 28 - 29
PLACE Eisenach + Liebenstein
Got to Eisenach at 8:00 was [crossed out: & had time] met by Aunt Anna + Uncle Alfred. Had time to walk to the Karlsplatz where stands the statue of Luther + the Nikolai Kirche - we walked thru an old "Thor" -- I always have to think of the picture postcards because it looks exactly like the "Thors" on those.  [crossed out:  Hellers villa in Liebens]  Caught just a glimpse of the outlines  of the Wartberg from the train.

PLACES VISITED
DATE June 29
PLACE Liebenstein
Heller's villa lies on the side of one of the Thuringian hills over-looking Liebenstein - just a mass of white houses + sloping red roofs caught in the embrace of the dark green hills. From my window I can look across the whole village to Altenstein the residence of the ex-duke of Meiningen. We took a short walk thru the forest in back of the house. It is for me indescribably beautiful - the dark

PLACES VISITED
DATE June 30 - 
PLACE Liebeustein
green of the pines is [[?...ened?] up  by White birch trunks  a few oaks + maples + the growth changes with every turn of the path. We saw the Burgstein an old "Raub ritter Schloss below which runs the road to Leipsic where the merchants used to be unwelcome guests of the castle's knights.
Walked up thru beautifully kept paths under huge birch trees + overhanging rocks to Schloss Altenstein the summer residence of the ex Dukes of Meiningen.

PLACE VISITED
DATE June 30
PLACE Liebenstein
Went thru the castle - Like Sans Souci it spells "voruehus heit?" especially the dining hall which is all "oak" from floor to ceiling. - Walked back thru the Morgen thor getting a panoramic view of the valley, the Rhön mountains etc. from a chevise? and house built by the old Duke and recently destroyed except for the four walls by revolutionists. Could see Burg Stein on the way home.

PLACES VISITED
DATE July 1
PLACE Liebenstein
It rained during the morning but cleared up in the afternoon + we walked thru the woods to Burg? Stein, the ruined "Alte Burg". It is just as I had always pictured ruins, built on top of the solid rock, perched way up, with the approach gradual but the castle itself surrounded by ravines. Pieces of the old outer wall are visible + the walls of the main building itself . One can still climb to

PLACES VISITED
DATE July 2
PLACE Eisenach
the second floor + look out over the valley.
July 2
---------
Started early in the morning. Reached Eisenach about 11 a.m. stopping at Salzurg? (very picturesque) where there are salt baths. Walked thru or rather up Eisenach - Mediaeval - all hills - + thru woods always uphill (615 ft above E.) To the Wartburg.  It is magnificently situated    Looking far out over the

PLACES VISITED
DATE
PLACE
Thuringian countryside - a different view from every window. Saw the castle from the inside -  Elizabeth's cut-out is a faithful image. The doors are marvelous - all carved I presume in oak. In the [?"Rüss kammer"?] are pieces of armor that date back to the crusades. Had I been thru here ten years ago I probably would have played knights there - I should like to now. Walked thru the Aweatal? along side of a

PLACES VISITED
DATE 
PLACE
little, fast flowing mountain brook + over it thru the Drachen schlusht? - a rock crevice no more than three feet wide, winding + dripping moisture - It was fun just like wandering through a labyrinth.

PLACES VISITED
DATE July 4, 1923
PLACE Jena -
Received an invitation to attend an official "Kneipe" of the Corps Franconia at Jena from the Lindenhagus.   The letter reached me the day of the Kneipe. I hired an auto to Eisenach + after much changing of trains reached Jena - alone. Asked the "Schaffner" the name of a good hotel, he named several + accidentally I picked the one where all university visitors stay. "Schwarze Bär". I introduced myself to two Frauken [sic] who were, as it happened also waiting for

the Lindenhayns.. In the evening we went to the Corps haus, a regular clubhouse, something like the fraternity houses in the states. We sat at one long table with the "erste Chargierte" at the head and the "Füchse" at the lower end. I can describe it as nothing less than "gemütlich." At that they tell me the life is quite different now, with much more studying + less time for galavanting around, partly

PLACES VISITED
DATE
PLACE July 5th, Jena
on account of the high price of beer, partly because these boys have to earn their living sooner + the cost of sending them thru the university is so high. - It was a most original way of celebrating the 4th of July. 

  In the morning I was shown around Jena + presented with an [?"ichter Ziegenbay neu stoek"?] with a dedication commemorating the occasion. Jena is "quaint" - everything is

PLACES  VISITED
DATE
PLACE
historical - Luther once had rooms in our hotel, etc. Motored to Heincar + looked at many noted things hurriedly + were back in Jena by three o'clock. The whole corps there made a Fucspartie to the Fuchsturm + we sat on top of the hill under trees at a wooden table + drank Lichtenhayner beer from wooden mugs. - Singing etc. 
Ate supper right out on the "marketplatz" at "Göbres." At the chorhaus in the evening and afterwards

PLACES VISITED
DATE
PLACE July 4 Jena
at the "Rose" a famous "Schanke". They took the ladies home early thru the dark Jena streets, silent until we came  The moon could just peep thru some of the narrowest alleys x. It was lovely - I got home early about 3 a.m. (dawn was breaking) but the corps + "Alte Herrn" stayed until morning. - The worst part of these things is saying goodbye. Back at Liebenstein today.

PLACES VISITED
DATE July 6 - 
PLACE Liebenstein
It is warm here - hot for here - but very comfortable for me. We heard a military Band at the Kurhaus Sunday - a dandy - and also met one of the "famous German lieutenants" a very nice, modest man wearing the iron cross "Erster Klasse" and the silver "[?schever?] verwundet" medal.

PLACES VISITED
DATE July 7-14
PLACE Liebenstein
It has been very hot. We took several walks which are lovely - went to Eisenach July 12 and saw the third part of the film "Frederikus Rex". - wonderful 
Prices are complicated Pork costs 56,000 marks a lb. a telegram with return paid costs 6,000 marks. - a shampoo 8,000 , an ivory girdle 120,000. Chocolate is almost as expensive as at home - about 84 if transfered to Amer. money.

PLACES VISITED
DATE July 16 - 
PLACE From Liebenstein to Dresden - 
To  Naumburg same route as from Berlin  
There were several families of "Eisenbahuen?" (refugees from the Ruhr) on the train + some of their stories are pitiful. Also in my cab a Bohemian from Prague, very intellectual, also incidentally an international ?alien? 
Spent three hours in Leipzig, raining, it is like Dresden as to "Platze" but not as many beautiful buildings. Had coffee at "Cafe [?Lelche?]."

W. Camillo Enterlein

PLACES VISITED
DATE July 17-18
PLACE Dresden
Dresden is more expensive than other places - it costs the equivalent of 2 gold marks a day extra (paid to police) besides "Beherberg [?cusstener?]" now. 
Met Alice + George Apfelbach honey mooning. - We all took a river boat up the Elbe to Wehlen - lovely scenery - walked to Teufelsgrund + Teufelskammer but didn't have time to get to the Bostic?

PLACES VISITED
DATE July 19, 1923
PLACE Dresden
Visited ?Linden......? & walked back thru unknown side streets finding my way to the Pragerstrasse again quite by accident.
Lunched with Mr. Arnold & went to theater in the evening with myself
to the "Schauspielhaus"  It is a beautiful place, very large and decorated in ivory & gold with a great candelabra like in our theaters.  Also the lights are dimmed gradually.
The house was filled & I

PLACES VISITED
DATE July 20
PLACE Dresden
believe not all by foreigners.  At the ticket office is the sign "Einlander bezhalen
crossed out: don 6' Teil des Preises, Müssen Ihren ausschein zeigen".  I paid 150,000 m. for 4th row, consequently a native would pay 25,000.
Also I pay 35000 M. for a Droschcke - all of 17 [?].
Mrs. Arnold - her aunt & her daughter, the aunt is a sculptress from Berlin & like all Berliners very sympathetic to me - & I drove to Meissen - saw the porcelain pieces
(the factory was closed & the Abrechtsburg -Meissen is lovely & quaint & old like

PLACES VISITED
DATE July 21
PLACE Dresden
Eisenack & Jena
Was at Arnholds for supper - They are very wealthy, have several autos & live in a little house with a gorgeous garden & view over Dresden - in Loschwitz 5 adorable children & four dogs.
Went by the [?"Weisser Hirsch"?] & Dr. Lachman's Sanatorium
Saturday
Shopping, walked thru the König Grosser Gartens, had supper in the Italienischer Garten. Succeeded in getting lost again.

PLACES VISITED
DATE July 22,
PLACE  Dresden -
Dr. Kurt Gruenier - corps friend of uncle o. - took me to (Dome) church, Catholic service, were facing choir + afterwards thru the Albertin univs the museum for sculpture. - I was at their house for dinner, they have a lovely collection of rugs, dishes, books, pictures, etc. - very talented family - awfully nice.
July 23-24-25
Bad Liebaustein - Took a long walk up to the "Hohe Kluege" from which we could see the whole Werratal - Walked with

PLACES VISITED
DATE July 27
PLACE Marburg
Mrs. Klug [crossed out:  & Dr.] and her cousin (cousins of Uncle Alfred). The doctor is a nuerologist and was very interesting.
July 27 - got to Marburg in the afternoon called for by Dr. Oskar Feyerabend??. His mother is lovely - also a nice step-grandaughter. Went to "Fredericus Rex" Parts I & II in the evening.
July 28 - Saturday - Stiftungsfest starting at 6 in Chorhaus - lovely place - castle above it - wonderful weather

Date July 29
Place Marburg
good music - nice company. plenty of partners - . Met Walter Bloeur,  author of “Gottesferne” etc. Danced until 2 o’clock with interruptions like a walk up to the castle by moonlight ste. 
Sunday
Walked thru town & saw the [?man?] in front of the drug store painted sky blue. - Festessen at the chor haus.  A lot of the students drank quantities of beer in the morning without the least effect on their

PLACES VISITED
DATE  July 29-30
PLACE - Marburg
manners.  -  Coffee at Vetter
Watched the coursers in the evening. Very "fererlich" particularly the Landes vater at [?] - the chargierten in their colored ribbons, swords, gloves, etc. A good many
looked ready to drop but they all behaved  just so until the Landesvater was ended. Then we ladies were escorted home.
Monday - 
post - long walk thru woods with Dr. F. & Miss Christians

PLACES VISITED
DATE  July 31
PLACE  En Route Munich
En route Munich from 9:15 a.m. to 1 a.m. the following morning with two hours in Frankfort & 2 hours delay of train because of a bad accident with many casualties near Hamburg. Munich is lovely - fountains & many "Platz".  I have a private room out of the heart of the city

PLACES VISITED
Date August 1-2
Place Munich - 
I have a nice room -- without bath - in the Adelheidstrasse -- in Schwabing (formerly at least the artists quarter).  Munich has more "Plätze" with trees than any city I have ever seen. 
Went thru the "Glaspalast" which has many modern Secession paintings -- some comprehensible even to me.
At Löwenbräu in evening. It was packed -- military band.

PLACES VISITED
DATE August 3 --
Place Starnbergersee
Left at 10 in the morning with Alice -- boat around lake -- had a lovely view of the mountains (real ones!) before it began to pour. The lake itself is deep green & very clear, the shores wooded with villas & castles --
Went to the Prinzregententheater in the evening & heard "Rheingold" -- a wonderful performance with the mermaids seemingly actually swimming & thunder lightning & rainbows. It is fine drama!

PLACES VISITED
Date August 4
Place Munich
Took the morning off for a bath!   Went to the Städtische Karl Müller Bad -- it is a small edition of the Roman thermae & the tubs are white tile & huge with clear sea-green water! Ate at Cafe Börse after wandering down thro the Thal, Marienplatz (old Rathaus) etc & in afternoon to  Karl Joseph Platz-- (Residenz,  Hauptpost) odeons Platz with Feldherrnhalle etc  Hofgarten -- blue sky, fountains, lovely murals in arcades, buildings, etc.

Starnberger See
[caption for photograph on preceding page]

PLACES VISITED
DATE  Aug 4-5
PLACE  Munich 
Saw the Austellungspark Hofbräuhaus & a little artists' [?] "Simplicissimus" by accident - (picked up two Munichers & paid their way - as newspaper corespondent.
They made excellent guides - also for Sunday -
Aug 5
Saw the parade of the "Fliegergedenkfeier" It was really thrilling -  wonderful military music - service & "Parade Marsch" - the soldiers  passing in review before
Ludendorff & his officers

PLACES VISITED
DATE  Aug 5
PLACE   Munich
Afternoon at Nymphenburg Evening in Löwenbräu - more music (supper at Gafelsperger & dinner at noon at Franziskaner keller) - coffee in evening at Maria Theresia café more
nice music  Also saw the Frauenkirche & Theatinerkirche in the morning
Aug 6
Deutsches Theatre - vaudeville with tables, food & beer.
Aug 7
Kaserne, outside of Maximilianeum & Siegfried

PLACES VISITED
DATE   August 8-9-10
PLACE   Berchtesgaden
Stayed at the Grand Hotel with a wonderful view of the Watzmann to one side + and the Leutersberg to the other where one sees the mountains from a distance they look beautiful, when one gets directly under them they are awe-inspiring in their height. The hotel is inhabited chiefly by Germans from Berlin + Hamburg ( Geld Juden). Went to the Königsee   It is much, much more

PLACES VISITED
DATE   Aug 9-10
PLACE  Berchtesgaden
beautiful than its pictures.  Annexed myself to an elderly couple & took a "Spaziergang" up to the beginning of the snowfields in raging heat. Got into the snow & almost froze.
Mountains to the left mountains in front the Watzman family to the right in the valley enormous "Felsblöcke" with trees growing out of them - 
Aug 10
Took a 5 hour Spaziergang from Berchtesgaden with the couple & a

Aug 21 - 22 - 23 Bodensee & Constance
Took a boat from Lindan to Constance. The day was wonderfully clear. deep blue lake, green shore, red & white houses - also to the South - including the  Hoher Suites & Finstershom Constance - old town - was as far as the Swiss border. Stayed at the Barbarossa Hotel (1183) but ate in the lovely Insel Hotel, once a famous monastery. - Saw the Island of Mainau- it is beautiful & the view different & lovely from every angle. --

PLACES VISITED
DATE Aug. 29
PLACE Freiburg
doctors whom we met here. 
Thursday Aug 30th Hanny and I went to Badenweiler-- from the ruins of the castle could see the Black Forest, Rhine valley & the Vosges mountains.
Saturday & Sunday walked with Hanny & the two doctors from Titi See to Schluchsee, then with Postanto to Sankt Blasiere (the doctors walked). Stayed over night in St. Blasiere & started on a gorgeous [?mushing?] Sunday morning thru the Albtal to Albruck (25 Kilometers)

PLACES VISITED

It was beautiful--Took train from Allbruck to Sächingen - saw Rhine Brücke & the Rhine itself - Home by way of Basel. --
Spent most of this week in Freiburg
Sept. 7 - went to Oberrimsingen with Fil. Ruf - ak unclear was welcomed by the peasants & got a good insight into their life.

went to Breisach Saturday + saw the Rhine with French colors on the bridge Town on a hill with fire towers, walls, etc. Saw the old instruments of torture. 

 Sunday - went to hear the Meistersänger - fine performance - enjoyed it more than the "Ring" more music for me  -

PLACES VISITED 
DATE November - 
PLACE Berlin 
VIsited the Schlosskirke financed & run by the Austrians for the benefit of the middle classes in Germany. - Left Berlin Sunday, November, 25 - for Brunswick via Hannover. Two hours in Hannover. Lovely city - old + new houses all mixed up &  a wonderful "Rathaus."

PLACES VISITED
DATE   November 26 - 28
PLACE Braunschweig
Stayed with the [?Heinal?] family - the city is still 3/4 mediaeval & the houses are all in wonderful condition considering their age.
It snowed & Brunswick in snow is like a Xmas postal card.
The "Burg Dankwarderode" is right in the center of the town & its foundations date from the 11th century -
Wed. Nov. 28 Traveling in  Germany today is

PLACES VISITED
DATE    Marburg
PLACE  Nov. 30 - Dec.
certainly not monotonous but one mustn't plan to reach any place at any certain time.   I started merrily from Braunschweig at noon - travelling 3rd class, second being way above American prices just at present - & after waiting two hours in a freezing station for the "Schnellzug"  which presumably went thru Marburg, I was informed I would have to get out in Cassel, wait 2 hours & then take a "Personerzug".
